  "response": "Using \"ex\" as a short form for \"example\" is relatively uncommon. Typically, \"ex\" is used as shorthand for \"exercise\" or \"former,\" but not for \"example.\" The more standard abbreviation for \"example\" is \"e.g.\" (from the Latin \"exempli gratia\"). It is important to use clear and widely recognized abbreviations to ensure your writing is easily understood by your audience.",
